This executive order, issued by President Barack Obama on December 21, 2012, states that all executive branch departments and agencies of the Federal Government will be closed and their employees excused from duty on Monday, December 24, 2012, except for those deemed necessary for national security, defense, or other public need. The order also clarifies the pay and leave of employees during this time and mandates that the Director of the Office of Personnel Management take necessary actions to implement the order. The order is subject to applicable law and the availability of appropriations and does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It also does not create any legal rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.